article.description: Kelan Martin had 21 points and eight rebounds, senior Austin Etherington scored a career-high 17 and Butler beat Creighton 88-75 Tuesday night.
article.headline: Butler's 13 3s keys 88-75 win over Creighton
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Kelan Martin had 21 points and eight rebounds, senior Austin Etherington scored a career-high 17 and Butler beat Creighton 88-75 Tuesday night. Martin and Etherington each hit four of Butler's 13 3-pointers as the Bulldogs made 48 percent from distance. Creighton was within 63-58 with 8:13 left but the Bluejays did not make another field goal for nearly three minutes and trailed 71-60 after Butler's 8-2 run. Andrew Chrabascz hit a wide open 3-pointer, off an assist from Kellen Dunham, to extend Butler's lead to 79-66 with three minutes left. Dunham finished with 16 points, Roosevelt Jones had 12 and Tyler Wideman 10 with four blocks for Butler (18-8, 7-7 Big East). Etherington and Dunham combined for three 3-pointers on three-straight Butler possessions for a 47-37 lead -- its first double-digit advantage -- early in the second half. Maurice Watson Jr. paced Creighton (17-10, 8-6) with 22 points and six assists.
